tart a new human necro and wander through the area to see what happens.  Up to this point nobody in any of the Freeports has conned any worse than dubious to me, except that dog Scraps they had running around East Freeport some months ago.<P>Eru_Necro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Woeleman</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Are you not KOS inside the bank? Are guards the only NPC's that attack? Thats good news if true. I'm a kill shy of 8 and will have gather shadows as soon as I level.<P>Thanks</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Volcanon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">only thing i see possible to do is dont screw over your DE faction since most necros that ive seen can walk into neriak and bank there without being killed by the guards</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Eru_Necro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I created a new human necro and wandered around the bank area in NFP.  I didn't see any new NPCs, and nobody attacked me.  I brought my main necro char back to NFP and he was ok too, but I did go bind myself at the back of the bank rather than outside the bank, just in case.  I'm starting to wander if this is just a hoax.<P>Eru_Necro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Frozen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">One npc (gnome) is inside the jewel shop (blue house outside marketarea). Seems like he doesn't go back to his spawn point if he aggros on someone.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zanzabar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well Ive been back to the NFP bank 3 times since the last patch with no ill effects, I have not seen any new NPC, BUT, I keep my hand on the FD button when I gate into the bank (bound in the front near the merchant), and when I run out to zone.  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Eru_Necro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The gnome (are you sure it's a gnome, or is it a dwarf, I couldn't see him well enough over the counter to tell) in the jewlry shop cons threatingly to the human test necro I created.  However, he only cons dubious to my Erudite necro.  I've improved my Erudite's faction with the dwarves enough that I'm no longer KOS off the boat in BB, so maybe that explains it.  <P>Does anyone know where the other new NPCs are, so I can check them out? <P>Eru_Necro </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">lyfe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've seen the gnome npc, but he didnt attack me.. I'm a d.e. necro who's warmly to paladin and mercants/bankers in n.fp.<P>I did however have a slight problem the other day when i logged in out front of the bank.. I got attacked by guards that normally like me..luckily being level 53 I was able to easily outrun them with jboots to the zone.  <P>This is an old bug that has been mentioned before.  When you first load in npc's react to your race and religion, then read faction modifiers (quests) that you have done.  So if you log in or gate in right next to a guard, he'll attack you before bothering to read your modified faction.  <P>Best advice is to bind and camp in an area that guards don't patrol.<P>Lyfe 53 Necro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Tvenya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It is true that there are new NPCs about that attack us.  I was attacked by a gnome rogue I believe in NFP.  He kept trying to backstab as I was running from him.  I made the zone pretty easily.<P>For the Necro who binds in NFP, here is a warning.  When you character first enters a zone, he enters with his base charisma, then his deeds are determined and that base charisma is adjusted.  So, for a split second, you can still be KOS there.  I would not bind anywhere near where guards hang out.  This has happened to me once, and I have seen it happen to others.  Abashi confirmed this is the way faction works.<P>Tvenya</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Eru_Necro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">That sounds like a bug!  They should fix that pronto.  I did rebind myself at the back of the bank.  I think my native faction for the people in the bank is OK to start with.  <P><BR>Eru_Necro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Grebble</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">That actually sounds realistic.  I mean if you were a freeport guard and all of a sudden WHAM there is a dark elf in your face you would probably swing first and ask questions later.  Then you look at the destroyed body in front of you and you would say "Oh, that guy WAS pretty nice.  Darn, too bad...."  Where as if you saw a dark elf in the distance you would have a chance to see if you knew that dark elf or not.  So if it was intended or not, they probably left it in for the realism of it.  /shrug</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zanzabar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I agree with Gribbe, sounds pretty realistic to me hehe.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Trcee</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I was in N FP last night to do some banking, and experienced no problems.  The servers even went down when I was in the bank, but upon logging back in the guards didn't attack me.  DE Necro, and the pallys are dubious to me. <P>(I've only done one stack of tumpy tonics...I guess when I hit 20 I'll head to EC some quiet morning and park Jabober in the middle of orc 2, do some faction farming.)<P>I have heard about the little gnome, though, and that he seems to be operating off of some faction noone else in N FP uses..."pissy gnome faction" someone called it.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
